The attacks ranged from simple location tracking to prompting users to install malicious Android apps. Despite lacking sophisticated techniques, the campaign's scale and duration were notable, operating undetected since late 2022. The compromised sites were linked to Kurdish media, political organizations, and the Rojava administration in Syria. A malicious Android app disguised as a news app was also discovered, capable of exfiltrating user data.
